EXTRACTED VALUE: A solid port that improves upon the PS3 version of the game but still falls short of the PC version and other games like it in the market.
Sadly, a fun game gets annoying due to omniscient AI and nebulous level design.
There are two types of people who will enjoy this game. People who like very accessible and simple to pick-up games, and people under the age of 18.
An undercooked mess of different genres that doesn't satisfy. [Issue#5, p.98]
If, like me, you’re vulnerable to anime/manga/JRPG cliché, then this game will be a guilty pleasure, but I’ll be surprised if you finish it.
